modules.description: Filters elements based on a predicate function, returning true or false for each instance of type `t`. Operates on custom data types defined within the module, allowing for selective processing. Used to isolate specific instances in a dataset for further transformation or analysis.
Returns the single instance of a type, ensuring global access. Works with any data type wrapped in a singleton pattern. Used to manage shared resources or configuration across an application.

Encodes refinement types using private type definitions to enforce invariants at the type level. Works with custom types wrapped in existential quantification to capture constraints. Enables safe manipulation of values like non-empty lists and bounded integers within strict type boundaries.

Checks if a type satisfies a set of constraints defined by its structure. Operates on abstract type representations to enforce or verify subtype relationships. Used to validate type hierarchies in compiler or type-checking workflows.
